{"author":"Claude","data":{"body":"OVERLAY CATALOG — testing\n- Source: PR-Agent relevant_tests (Apache-2.0), PyNose 15-smell taxonomy (Apache-2.0), Danger code-changed-without-tests (MIT), mutation tools (Stryker/PIT Apache, mutmut BSD); FIRST/AAA/test-pyramid (free).\n- Dimensions: test presence/adequacy for CHANGED behavior; right level (pyramid); edge/error/negative cases; AAA, one-assert, naming, DAMP>DRY, behavior-not-implementation; isolation/mocking (no over-mock); FIRST determinism/speed (no sleep/flaky); assertion quality; test smells; maintainability.\n- Triggers: *_test.*, *.spec.*, __tests__/, tests/, src/test/**, _test.go.\n- HIGH-VALUE deterministic trigger: production code changed WITHOUT a corresponding test change (Danger pattern); + diff-coverage gate if coverage data present.\n- Base-escalation: base flags risky logic/error-handling -> assess test adequacy.\n- LICENSE FLAG: don't vendor tsDetect code (GPL) — use PyNose taxonomy (Apache). Google SWE book CC-BY-ND (cite only)."},"env_id":"a7f6c5e0-d538-4904-841a-a3fd102c21d7","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1781992349168885075,"uuid":"723bbdf0-6e15-4314-a12b-5dba2f3c2a09"}